-- Yandex, Google Weekly Internet Search Shares Advance in Russia
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-09-17T19:24:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/yandex-google-weekly-internet-search-shares-advance-in-russia.html
Yandex NV (YNDX) ’s share of Russia’s
Internet searches rose in the week to Sept. 16 and the portion
of Google Inc.’s searches also advanced, while  Mail.ru Group
Ltd. (MAIL) ’s share remained steady, according to Liveinternet.ru.  The share for Yandex, the owner of Russia’s most-used
search engine, rose to 60.5 percent, from 60.4 percent in the
previous week,  Liveinternet , an Internet service provider and
researcher, said on its website today. Yandex’s search share
averaged 60.6 percent over the past four weeks, according to
Liveinternet.ru.  Russian searches using Google, the world’s largest Web-
search provider, rose to 26.8 percent in the week to Sept. 16
from 26.6 percent, for a four-week average of 26.6 percent, the
data show.  The portion of Mail.ru Group Ltd., the largest Russian-
language Internet company, was unchanged at 8.2 percent. The
four-week average was also 8.2 percent, the data showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
